                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14460639" author="spullara" created="Mon, 3 Jan 2005 20:48:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This because we use BeanInfo in the MetaClasses.  We probably have to add special logic to get around this in the case you actually ask for BeanInfo itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14462935" author="roblight" created="Thu, 12 Jul 2007 08:32:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any known work arounds?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463346" author="guillaume" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2007 06:21:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s still a problem, please reopen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463486" author="roblight" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2007 10:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still broken in 1.1-rc-1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Was any code changed to address this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463503" author="guillaume" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2007 11:10:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ll fix it in 1.6.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477804" author="paulk" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2008 17:18:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have made a change to this which appears to work in most simple cases but needs further testing. If you have a medium complexity test case to try against this, that would be great. You can get a jar/distribution with the change from &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.canoo.com/groovy&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.canoo.com/groovy&lt;/a&gt; in a few minutes time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478059" author="paulk" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 19:50:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jochen, I am tempted to close this off unless we get further feedback that more is required. Certainly, the supplied script works fine now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
